    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder [Player Name],

Your actions at Sentinel Stand have once again supplied the rumormongers of the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url] with stories to peddle.  Some seem to think that your cunning twist of legalese intended to display some great support for the people of Stalwart. That, of course, only leads to speculation about which people of Stalwart you intended to benefit: the unbridled upstarts or the corrupt old queens. Others foolishly believe you unraveled the Overlord's [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] to prove that you could, as if a sliver of cleverness could bring [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] low.

As a scholar, I prefer primary sources to gossip, so allow me to ask you plainly: why did you choose to spare the child?

- Fatebinder Rhogalus
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>Tell him it was the right thing to do.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>Tell him it was purely political.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>Tell him to mind his own business.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder Rhogalus,

When faced with the choice to save a child or consign it to death, I chose to save it. That does not seem so strange a thing to me. Either decision would have fulfilled the Overlord's will: the last ruling house of Stalwart met its end in the [url=glossary:blade grave]Blade Grave[/url].

You need read nothing more into it than that.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder Rhogalus,

The blood of [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url], Archon of War, flows through that child's veins. It should take no scholar of history or governance to recognize the potential in protecting it. The Archon appreciates family above all else. Why would I deprive him of a grandchild born of the ruling family of Stalwart if I could do so without shirking my duty to the Overlord?

I do not make a habit of discarding gifts of fortune.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder Rhogalus,

You will have to look to the rumormongers for your answers. I keep counsel on this matter only with myself.

- Fatebinder [Player Name]
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
