    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder [Player Name],

You display curious empathy for those who name you enemy. I sincerely hope that history remembers it as one of your critical strengths rather than your most dire weakness.

Remember always that the Overlord favors efficacy over empathy. Rare is the Fatebinder who delivers both.

- Fatebinder Rhogalus
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder [Player Name],

I suspected that your cleverness did not end at the use of local customs of abdication. You make no mistake in your estimate of the child's probable import to the Archon of War. Its continued existence illuminates a gap in his armor - regardless of whether he cherishes the child or resents it.

I would warn you to play such games carefully, but you seem to have your eye on the board.

- Fatebinder Rhogalus
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dear Fatebinder [Player Name],

You disappoint me. I will interpret this as an unwillingness to set your thoughts to parchment, prone to interception as such missives are, rather than an attempt to avoid indicting yourself to an agent of the court.

Remember: nothing remains unrevealed forever.

- Fatebinder Rhogulas</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
